Again I want to stress that I have no connection or affiliation with the show “SLEDGE HAMMER”, its producers, writers, creators, directors, etc. I’m just a big fan of the show and the .44 magnum Inspector Hammer used on the show. title: For Sale:  Fabrique Nationale -- FN model 1910, General Sumner's Personal handgun
postcontent: This FN model 1910 rig belonged to Lieutenant General Gordon Sumner JR. General Sumner was born on July 23, 1924 and died on April 5, 2012. General Sumner as graduate of US Military Academy was involved in many important tasks and projects from WWII through Vietnam and beyond. He was wounded in Korea and captured but escaped two days later. He was a speech writer for General Douglas MacArthur in Korea. As a Colonel in Vietnam commanded the 25th Infantry Division. Later in his career he was a Military Assistant to the Secretary of Defense Melvin Laird. In 2004 he published a book indicating his experiences in military titled "Marching ON" A General's Tales of War and Diplomacy. There are a few references to his pistol in his book on pages 42-45. General Sumner has his name inscribed on the right side of the pistol. The gun comes with original holster and an extra magazine. There are several articles about him on the Internet, I'll forward the articles, pictures and the book to the buyer. The rig is in nice shape with excellent bore. If you want a small historic gun or a nice carry gun here is your chance.

postcontent: CHECK TO SEE AVAILABILITY OR TO PURCHASE>Bergara Premier Series LRP 20" Barrel .308 Winchester MFG # BPR17308C UPC Code # REDACTED32  Bergara Premier Series LRP 20" Barrel .308 Winchester MFG # BPR17308C UPC Code # REDACTED32  Watch our video on the Vergara LRP .308 "Quality is not an act, it is a habit." -William James Durant Customization isn't for everyone, but custom quality should be. The Premier Series delivers just that. Think of their Premier Series Rifles as an extension to their Custom Series Rifles, but with standardized features for greater efficiences in parts production and assembly - providing near custom-quality rifles at prices that are affordable to serious shooters. The Premier Series LRP rifle features a Bergara Branded aluminum chassis made in partnership XLR Industries. The Chassis is CNC machined from solid 6061-T6 aluminum, and features an AR15 style grip, adjustable length of pull, adjustable comb height, and the butt plate can be canted to give a precise fit to the shooter in virtually any shooting position. What makes this rifle so special you may ask? Well, Bergara uses Premium 416 stainless steel barrels, which receive a proprietary honing process at their barrel-making facility, at which point they continue through another four stages of production to produce the most accurate production barrel they could possibly make. Upon completion, the barrel receives a Cerakote finish and is coupled with the Bergara Premier action. This process is completed at their facility in Lawrenceville, GA USA. The Bergara LRP weighs around 10 pounds, comes with an AICS detachable five-round magazine, a Timney 517 flat trigger, as well as a Talley 20 MOA rail. The LRP rifle also comes standard with threaded muzzles (5/8x24) and a Dead Air Armament Key Lock muzzle break installed. Barrel lengths range from a 20" barrel on the .308, 22" on the 6.5 Creedmoor, and 24" on the 6mm Creedmoor. It has a guaranteed capability of producing sub-1.0 MOA or better groups at 100 yards with factory match grade ammunition. Every Premier Series Rifle is qualified for accuracy prior to leaving their facility. Each rifle must shoot three consecutive 3-shot groups, all sub-1.0 MOA to qualify. Once completed, they include a copy of the target itself, as well as the information on the factory load used, the date, and the shooter who qualified this rifle.
